Durban - South African bowler Mondli Khumalo has defied all odds, making a speedy recovery at the Southmead Hospital in Bristol, in the UK, after suffering a brain injury over a week ago. Khumalo underwent three surgical operations, and his agent has shared that the youngster is now able to stand on his own and catch a cricket ball. The 20-year-old is currently on a short-term contract to play for the North Petherton Cricket Club. He left South Africa in April and was due back in August. Just 1 week after his 3rd brain op in 3 days, Mondli has today got his ability to catch back, and stand unaided! This boy is incredible #mondlikhumalo pic.twitter.com/MlFKNOqxRw Two weeks ago, the youngster got into an altercation with a 27-year-old man who allegedly head-butted him a few times and punched him in the head. The man was arrested but released on a warning. On Tuesday, Khumalo’s mother and uncle flew to the UK and they are now by his side. Read the full story about Khumalo’s recovery in the Sunday Tribune this coming Sunday. SUNDAY TRIBUNE